The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques in enabling long-term autonomy in robotic systems. The paper covers various sub-disciplines of AI such as navigation & mapping, perception, knowledge representation & reasoning, planning, interaction, and learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AI techniques such as machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY) in enabling long-term autonomy in robotic systems. Finally, the paper also discusses the integration of these techniques within long-running robotic systems, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
